---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import SectionTitle from "../components/SectionTitle.astro";
import TextSection from "../components/TextSection.astro";
import Collapsible from "../components/collapsible.astro";
---

<BaseLayout>
    <SectionTitle text="Interests and hobbies" />

    <TextSection
        text="Here, I'm a bit of a Renaissance person when it comes to my free time. Let's dive in and explore the weird and wonderful things that keep me occupied when I'm not pretending to be productive!"
    />

    <Collapsible label="- Reading">
        <TextSection
            text="Well, well, well, my dear friends, gather round and let me tell you about the wonders of reading. As a lifelong reader, I can assure you that reading is one of the most rewarding hobbies you can have. Whether you're cozying up with a captivating novel on a dreary day or immersing yourself in an academic textbook for hours on end, reading is a constant source of comfort and intellectual stimulation."
        />
        <TextSection
            text="Back in my school days, reading was a real drag. We were assigned books not for their literary merit, but for their ability to teach us vocab or history. We had to read to memorize, not to discuss ideas. The joy of reading was lost in the monotony of analysis and regurgitation."
        />
        <TextSection
            text="But then, I discovered the joy of reading for pleasure, without anyone telling me what to read. Oh, the freedom! I was finally able to explore genres and authors that truly interested me, and it was a game-changer. It reminded me that sometimes the best things in life require a little rebellion against the status quo."
        />
        <TextSection
            text="Books have been so much more to me than just entertainment or an academic exercise, a refuge from the world, a place to reflect and process emotions. Sometimes they challenge assumptions and broaden perspective. Other times,they can teach you empathy and understanding people and cultures different from your own."
        />
        <TextSection
            text="I remember reading Animal Farm for the first time and being completely drawn into the story of the farm animals and their struggle for power. The characters were so well-developed that I felt like I was right there in the middle of the action, watching it all unfold. And Crime and Punishment? Don't even get me started! Dostoevsky weaves together philosophy, psychology, and suspense like a true master."
        />
        <TextSection
            text="Now, hold on to your hats, because here's the zinger: academic textbooks. I know, I know, they're as thrilling as watching paint dry, but hear me out. When you read an academic book, it's like having a knowledgeable friend, or even a mentor, talking to you and guiding you through a topic. And when you finally grasp a difficult concept, the feeling of accomplishment is unparalleled."
        />
        <TextSection
            text="So, my friends, if you're not already an avid reader, I implore you to give it a try. Don't worry about what others might think of your choices or whether they fit into some prescribed curriculum. Just read what you love and enjoy the ride. And with that, I'm off to curl up with a good book..."
        />
        <TextSection text="" />
        <TextSection text="" />
        <TextSection text="" />
    </Collapsible>
</BaseLayout>
